          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <section id="what-it-means" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>What Product Listing AI Optimisation Means</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>AI optimisation for product listings is the process of structuring every layer of product data — schema markup, listing descriptions, specification content, and data feeds — so that AI engines can extract accurate, complete product information and cite it confidently in generated answers.</strong>
          It is more granular than broader ecommerce GEO because it focuses specifically on the product data layer: the individual page,
          the individual listing, the individual structured data object.
        </p>

        <p>
          When a user asks an AI engine "what is the best DSLR camera for beginners under £600", the system retrieves candidate pages
          and extracts product data from them. The quality of that extraction depends directly on how the product data is structured.
          A product page with incomplete schema, a description that leads with "introducing the revolutionary X500 camera", and a
          specifications section buried three screens down will be extracted poorly — or not at all. A page with complete Product schema,
          a declarative opening description, and specifications in a structured table will be extracted with high confidence and cited accurately.
        </p>

        <p>
          This page focuses specifically on the product data and listing content layer. For the broader strategy of getting an ecommerce
          brand cited in AI answers — including brand-level entity authority and category page editorial content — see our guide to
          <a href="/ai-optimisation-ecommerce/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">AI optimisation for ecommerce</a>.
          For the full GEO framework, see our guide to
          <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <section id="product-schema" class="anchor-top mb-16">
        <div class="prose-dark">
          <h2>Product Schema: Complete Specification</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Product schema in JSON-LD is the machine-readable foundation of product AI citation.</strong>
            AI retrieval systems parse JSON-LD before body content because it provides unambiguous, structured signals
            that do not require natural language interpretation. A product page without valid Product schema relies entirely
            on the AI system's ability to parse prose — a significantly less reliable extraction mechanism.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                <th scope="col" class="py-3 pr-4 text-left font-semibold text-ink-50">Property</th>
                <th scope="col" class="py-3 pr-4 text-left font-semibold text-ink-50">Type</th>
                <th scope="col" class="py-3 pr-4 text-left font-semibold text-ink-50">Required for AI</th>
                <th scope="col" class="py-3 text-left font-semibold text-ink-50">Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/5">
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">name</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Text</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Essential</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">Exact product name as sold</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">brand</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Brand</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Essential</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">Use Brand type with name property</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">description</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Text</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Essential</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">Factual, declarative; avoid marketing language</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">sku</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Text</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Recommended</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">Unique identifier; helps deduplication</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">image</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">ImageObject</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Essential</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">Include width, height, url</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">offers</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Offer</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Essential</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">price, priceCurrency, availability, url</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">aggregateRating</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">AggregateRating</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Essential</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">ratingValue, bestRating, reviewCount</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">additionalProperty</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">PropertyValue</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Recommended</td>
                <td class="py-3 text-ink-300">Technical specs; one PropertyValue per attribute</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-accent-400">gtin13 / gtin8</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Text</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-300">Recommended</td>
